.\" Man page for oci2bin
.\" Generate HTML: groff -man -Thtml doc/oci2bin.1
.\" Generate PDF:  groff -man -Tpdf  doc/oci2bin.1 > oci2bin.pdf
.TH OCI2BIN 1 "2026-03-12" "oci2bin 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
oci2bin \- convert Docker/OCI images into self-contained rootless container executables
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SS Building
.SY oci2bin
.OP \-\-arch ARCH
.OP \-\-cache
.OP \-\-layer IMAGE
.OP \-\-strip
.OP \-\-add\-file HOST:CONTAINER
.OP \-\-add\-dir HOST:CONTAINER
.OP \-\-oci\-dir DIR
.OP \-\-pull\-with docker|podman|skopeo
.I IMAGE\c
.RI [: TAG ]
.RI [ OUTPUT ]
.YS
.PP
.SY oci2bin
.I SUBCOMMAND
.RI [ ARGS ]
.YS
.
.SS Running the generated binary
.SY ./OUTPUT
.OP \-v HOST:CONTAINER
.OP \-e KEY=VALUE
.OP \-\-net host|none|container:\fIPID\fR
.OP \-\-ipc host|container:\fIPID\fR
.OP \-\-entrypoint PATH
.OP \-\-workdir PATH
.OP \-\-user UID\fR[:\fIGID\fR]
.OP \-\-hostname NAME
.OP \-\-secret HOST_FILE\fR[:\fICONTAINER_PATH\fR]
.OP \-\-env\-file FILE
.OP \-\-tmpfs PATH
.OP \-\-device /dev/HOST\fR[:\fICONTAINER\fR]
.OP \-\-read\-only
.OP \-\-init
.OP \-\-detach
.OP \-\-ssh\-agent
.OP \-\-cap\-drop CAP
.OP \-\-cap\-add CAP
.OP \-\-ulimit TYPE=N
.OP \-\-no\-seccomp
.OP \-\-
.RI [ CMD " [" ARGS ]]
.YS
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B oci2bin
converts any Docker or OCI image into a single, self-contained ELF64 executable.
The output file is also a valid POSIX tar archive accepted by
.BR "docker load" ,
making it a polyglot binary.
.PP
The generated binary requires only
.BR tar (1)
on the target machine \(em no Docker daemon, no runtime, no installation.
It runs the container rootlessly using Linux user namespaces.
.PP
The container process appears as UID\~0 inside the container; on the host it runs
as the invoking user with no elevated privileges.
.PP
This man page summarizes the most common options and subcommands. The complete
and authoritative reference is the project
.B README
and the documentation site under
.IR docs/ ,
which always track the current feature set.
.
.SH BUILD OPTIONS
These options are passed to the
.B oci2bin
CLI wrapper at build time.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-arch " ARCH"
Build a binary for
.I ARCH
(either
.B x86_64
or
.BR aarch64 ).
When building for a foreign architecture from x86_64, the
.B aarch64\-linux\-gnu\-gcc
cross-compiler is required.
The sysroot defaults to
.IR /usr/aarch64\-redhat\-linux/sys\-root/fc43 ;
override with the
.B AARCH64_SYSROOT
environment variable.
.
.TP
.B \-\-cache
Cache the output in
.IR ~/.cache/oci2bin/<image>_<digest>/output .
Repeated builds of the same image are instant.
The cache key includes the first 12 hex characters of the image's sha256 digest
so tag updates are detected automatically.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-layer " IMAGE"
Overlay additional image layers on top of the base image.
Layers are applied in order; the image config
.RI ( Cmd ", " Entrypoint ", " Env )
from the last
.B \-\-layer
argument overrides the base if non-null.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.B \-\-strip
Remove documentation, man pages, locale data, and package caches before
packaging.
Affected paths:
.IR usr/share/doc/ ,
.IR usr/share/man/ ,
.IR usr/share/info/ ,
.IR usr/share/locale/ ,
.IR usr/share/i18n/ ,
.IR var/cache/apt/ ,
.IR var/lib/apt/lists/ ,
.IR tmp/ .
.
.TP
.BI \-\-add\-file " HOST:CONTAINER"
Inject a file from
.I HOST
into the image at
.I CONTAINER
path at build time.
The file is embedded as an extra layer on top of the image layers.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-add\-dir " HOST:CONTAINER"
Inject a directory from
.I HOST
into the image at
.I CONTAINER
path at build time.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-oci\-dir " DIR"
Build from an OCI image layout directory instead of pulling via Docker.
Compatible with images produced by
.BR skopeo (1),
.BR crane (1),
and
.BR buildah (1).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-pull\-with " docker|podman|skopeo"
Force the pull backend used by the default
.I IMAGE
build instead of auto-detecting (order: docker, podman, skopeo).
.B skopeo
pulls daemonlessly
.RB ( "skopeo copy docker://IMAGE oci:\&\&..." ),
so no container engine is required.
.B \-\-pull\-with skopeo
does not support
.BR \-\-layer ", " \-\-offline\-only ,
or cosign verification, and aborts rather than skipping them.
.
.TP
.B \-\-squash
Merge all image layers into a single squashed layer before packaging
(combine with
.B \-\-compress
to pick the layer codec).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-entrypoint " VALUE" \fR, \fB\-\-cmd " VALUE"
Override the embedded image Entrypoint/Cmd at build time.
.I VALUE
is a JSON array
.RB ( [\fB"a","b"\fR] )
or a shell-split string.
.B \-\-entrypoint
without
.B \-\-cmd
clears the image's default Cmd.
.
.TP
.B \-\-compress\-binary zstd
Recompress the embedded payload as one zstd frame to shrink the output.
Requires
.BR zstd (1)
at run time; the payload is then opaque to
.BR "docker load" .
.
.TP
.B \-\-encrypt \fR[\fB\-\-recipient \fIPUB\fR]\fR, \fB\-\-passphrase
Encrypt the embedded image with
.BR age .
At run time supply the identity via
.B OCI2BIN_IDENTITY
or the passphrase via
.BR OCI2BIN_PASSWORD [ _FILE ].
.
.TP
.B \-\-reproducible \fR/\fB \-\-offline\-only
Produce byte-identical output across builds;
.B \-\-offline\-only
additionally refuses any registry fetch and records a hermetic marker.
.
.TP
.B \-\-verify\-cosign \fR/\fB \-\-require\-cosign
Verify the source image's cosign signature before building (abort on failure
with
.BR \-\-require\-cosign ).
.
.SH RUNTIME OPTIONS
These options are passed to the generated binary at run time.
.
.SS Volume mounts
.TP
.BI \-v " HOST:CONTAINER"
Bind-mount
.I HOST
path into the container at
.IR CONTAINER .
The container path must be absolute and must not contain
.BR .. .
May be repeated (up to 32).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-secret " HOST_FILE\fR[:\fICONTAINER_PATH\fR]"
Bind-mount a single host file into the container read-only.
If
.I CONTAINER_PATH
is omitted, the file lands at
.IR /run/secrets/<basename> .
Enforced with
.BR MS_RDONLY | MS_NOEXEC | MS_NOSUID | MS_NODEV .
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-tmpfs " PATH"
Mount a fresh in-memory filesystem at
.I PATH
inside the container.
.I PATH
must be absolute and must not contain
.BR .. .
Useful for writable scratch space when
.B \-\-read\-only
is active.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-device " /dev/HOST\fR[:\fICONTAINER\fR]"
Expose a host device node inside the container.
.I HOST
must start with
.IR /dev/ .
.I CONTAINER
defaults to
.I HOST
if omitted.
.BR mknod (2)
is attempted first; on failure a bind mount is used.
May be repeated.
.
.SS Process and environment
.TP
.BI \-e " KEY=VALUE"
Set an environment variable inside the container.
.I KEY
must not be empty.
.TP
.BI \-e " KEY"
Pass
.I KEY
from the host environment.
If the variable is not set on the host, a warning is printed and it is skipped.
May be repeated (up to 64).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-env\-file " FILE"
Load
.I KEY=VALUE
pairs from
.IR FILE .
Blank lines and lines beginning with
.B #
are ignored.
May be repeated; processed before
.B \-e
flags.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-entrypoint " PATH"
Override the image's OCI entrypoint.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-workdir " PATH"
Set the working directory inside the container.
Overrides the image's
.BR WorkingDir .
Defaults to
.B /
if neither is set.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-user " UID\fR[:\fIGID\fR]"
Run the container process as numeric
.I UID
(and optional
.IR GID ).
Both values must be integers \(<=\~65534.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-hostname " NAME"
Set the hostname inside the UTS namespace.
Defaults to
.BR oci2bin .
.
.TP
.BI \-\-ulimit " TYPE=N"
Set a resource limit via
.BR setrlimit (2).
Both soft and hard limits are set to
.IR N .
Supported types:
.BR nofile ,
.BR nproc ,
.BR cpu ,
.BR as ,
.BR fsize .
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.B \-\-init
Run a zombie-reaping init as PID\~1.
The entrypoint is forked as a child; the parent loop reaps zombies.
.BR SIGTERM ,
.BR SIGINT ,
.BR SIGHUP ,
.BR SIGUSR1 ,
and
.B SIGUSR2
are forwarded to the child.
.
.TP
.BR \-\-detach ", " \-d
Fork the container to the background, print the child PID to stdout, and exit.
Calls
.BR setsid (2)
and redirects stdin from
.IR /dev/null .
.
.TP
.B \-\-ssh\-agent
Forward the host
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
Unix socket into the container at
.IR /run/ssh-agent.sock .
Sets
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
inside the container.
Skipped silently if
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
is unset or points to a non-socket.
.
.TP
.B \-\-
End of option parsing.
Remaining arguments are treated as the command and its arguments.
.
.SS Networking and IPC namespaces
.TP
.B \-\-net host
Share the host network stack (default).
.
.TP
.B \-\-net none
Create an isolated network namespace with only a loopback interface.
.
.TP
.B \-\-net slirp \fR/\fB \-\-net pasta
Userspace outbound networking in a private namespace via
.BR slirp4netns (1)
or
.BR pasta (1).
.
.TP
.BI \-p " HOST:CTR"
Publish a port (implies
.BR "\-\-net slirp" ).
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-dns " IP" \fR, \fB\-\-dns\-search " DOMAIN" \fR, \fB\-\-add\-host " HOST:IP"
Write a custom resolver and add
.I /etc/hosts
entries inside the container.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-allow\-egress " HOST:PORT|CIDR:PORT"
Default-deny egress allowlist (requires
.BR \-\-net " slirp/pasta " "and " nft );
fails closed. May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-net " container:" PID
Join the network namespace of the process with PID
.IR PID .
The container shares all network interfaces, routing tables, and port bindings
with that process.
.I PID
must be a positive integer.
.
.TP
.B \-\-ipc host
Share the host IPC namespace (default).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-ipc " container:" PID
Join the IPC namespace of the process with PID
.IR PID ,
sharing SysV semaphores, message queues, and
.BR shmget (2)
shared memory segments.
.
.SS Isolation
.TP
.B \-\-read\-only
Mount the rootfs read-only via overlayfs.
Writes go to a temporary upper layer discarded on exit.
Falls back to read-write with a warning if overlayfs is unavailable.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-cap\-drop " CAP"
Drop capability
.I CAP
from the bounding and effective sets.
Pass
.B all
to drop all capabilities.
.I CAP
is case-insensitive; the
.B CAP_
prefix is optional.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-cap\-add " CAP"
Add capability
.I CAP
as an ambient capability so it survives
.BR exec (2).
Use after
.B \-\-cap\-drop all
to selectively restore capabilities.
.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-seccomp
Disable the default seccomp-BPF syscall filter.
The filter blocks: kexec_load, reboot, syslog, perf_event_open, bpf,
add_key, request_key, keyctl, userfaultfd, pivot_root, ptrace,
process_vm_readv, process_vm_writev, init_module, finit_module.
.B PR_SET_NO_NEW_PRIVS
is always set regardless of this flag.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-seccomp\-profile " FILE"
Load a Docker-compatible JSON seccomp profile instead of the default filter.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-gen\-seccomp " FILE"
Trace the workload's syscalls and write a least-privilege profile to
.IR FILE .
.
.TP
.BI \-\-seccomp\-deny\-write " PATH"
Bind-mount
.I PATH
read-only inside the container. May be repeated.
.
.TP
.B \-\-landlock \fR/\fB \-\-no\-landlock
Force or disable the Landlock filesystem sandbox (default: auto when the kernel
supports it).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-security\-opt " apparmor=" PROFILE \fR| \fBlabel=\fITYPE:VAL\fR
Apply an AppArmor profile or SELinux exec label (compile-time support required).
.
.SS Resources and state
.TP
.BI \-\-memory " SIZE" \fR, \fB\-\-cpus " N" \fR, \fB\-\-pids\-limit " N"
cgroup v2 hard limits on memory, CPU, and PID count for the whole container
tree.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-size " NAME"
Apply a resource preset
.RB ( pi\-zero ", " pi4 ", " vps\-small ", " vps\-medium ", " beefy ", " auto )
that fills unset
.BR \-\-memory / \-\-cpus / \-\-pids\-limit .
.
.TP
.BI \-\-ulimit " TYPE=N"
Set a
.BR setrlimit (2)
limit
.RB ( nofile ", " nproc ", " cpu ", " as ", " fsize ).
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-overlay\-persist " DIR"
Keep the overlay upper layer in
.I DIR
so writes survive between runs.
.
.SS Observability
.TP
.BI \-\-metrics\-socket " PATH"
Export Prometheus cgroup metrics over a Unix socket at
.IR PATH .
.
.TP
.BI \-\-notify " URL" \fR, \fB\-\-notify\-name " NAME"
Fire lifecycle notifications to an
.BR ntfy / gotify / discord / slack
or generic
.B https
sink.
.I NAME
labels the payloads. May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-audit\-log " FILE"
Append newline-delimited JSON lifecycle events to
.IR FILE " (" \- " = stderr)."
.
.TP
.BI \-\-clock\-offset " SECS"
Shift the container's monotonic/boottime clocks via a time namespace.
.
.TP
.B \-\-doctor
Report whether the current host can run the binary in namespace mode
(unprivileged user namespaces and the AppArmor/clone knobs,
.BR newuidmap / newgidmap " + " /etc/subuid ,
seccomp, Landlock, cgroup v2,
.BR tar ,
and
.I /dev/kvm
for
.BR \-\-vm ),
then exit.
Read-only: it never extracts the image or creates namespaces, and exits
non-zero if a blocking issue is found.
Unlike
.B oci2bin doctor
(which inspects the build host) this reflects the actual runtime host.
.
.SS Supervision, health, and devices
.TP
.BI \-\-restart " POLICY"
Supervise and relaunch the workload.
.I POLICY
is
.BR no ", " on\-failure [: \fIN\fR],
.BR always ", or " unless\-stopped .
.
.TP
.B \-\-health
Run the image HEALTHCHECK on its interval; mark the container unhealthy after
repeated failures and (with
.BR \-\-restart )
restart it. Override with
.BR \-\-health\-cmd ", " \-\-health\-interval ", " \-\-health\-timeout ", " \-\-health\-retries ", " \-\-health\-start\-period ;
disable with
.BR \-\-no\-health .
.
.TP
.BI \-\-gpus " all|N|CDI" \fR, \fB\-\-cdi\-device " KIND=DEVICE"
Expose GPUs or other Container Device Interface devices, applying the matching
CDI spec's device nodes, mounts, and environment.
.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-host\-dev
Skip bind-mounting the standard host
.I /dev
nodes into the container.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-profile " NAME"
Apply a runtime defaults preset:
.BR dev ", " prod ", or " locked\-down .
Later flags override the profile.
.
.TP
.B \-\-vm \fR[\fB\-\-vmm \fIVMM\fR]
Run the container in a hardware-isolated microVM (libkrun, or
.B cloud\-hypervisor
via
.BR \-\-vmm ).
Requires
.IR /dev/kvm .
.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B oci2bin inspect \fIBINARY\fR
Display OCI metadata embedded in
.IR BINARY :
image name, architecture, layer count, entrypoint, command, environment,
working directory, build digest, and build timestamp.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin list \fR[\fB\-\-json\fR]
List all cached binaries with image name, digest, size, and build date.
.B \-\-json
emits machine-readable JSON.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin prune \fR[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
Remove outdated cache entries, keeping only the most recently built binary
for each image name.
.B \-\-dry\-run
shows what would be deleted without deleting.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin diff \fIOLD\fR \fINEW\fR
Compare the filesystem contents of two oci2bin binaries.
Output lines are prefixed with
.BR + " (added), " \- " (removed), or " M " (modified)."
Exits 0 if identical, 1 if there are differences.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin diff\-fs \fIOVERLAY_PATH\fR
Classify an overlayfs upperdir (from a
.B \-\-overlay\-persist
run) as docker-diff-style A/D entries.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin explain \fIBINARY\fR \fR[\fB\-\-json\fR]
Combined report: embedded metadata (secrets redacted) plus a host-capability
check for what the binary needs to run.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin doctor \fR[\fB\-\-json\fR]
Probe the host for the toolchain and kernel features oci2bin uses and print a
fix command for each missing piece.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin sbom \fIBINARY\fR
Generate a Software Bill of Materials for the embedded image.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin reconstruct \fISRC\fR \fR[\fB\-\-output \fIPATH\fR]
Rebuild a polyglot from a Docker image or saved tar that carries an embedded
loader.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin push \fIBINARY\fR \fIREF\fR
Push the embedded image payload to an OCI registry reference.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin exec \fIPID\fR \fR[\fB\-\-\fR] \fICMD\fR ...
Run a command inside a running container's namespaces (needs
.BR nsenter ).
.
.TP
.B oci2bin ps
List running named containers.
.B oci2bin stop \fINAME\fR
and
.B oci2bin logs \fR[\fB\-f\fR] \fINAME\fR
stop and tail them.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin top \fR[\fB\-\-once\fR] [\fB\-\-interval \fISEC\fR]
Live per-container resource stats.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin systemd \fIBINARY\fR \fR[\fB\-\-user\fR] [\fB\-\-restart \fIPOLICY\fR]
Print a systemd unit file for the binary.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin healthcheck \fIBINARY\fR \fR[\fB\-\-pid \fIPID\fR]
Run the image's declared HEALTHCHECK once and report the result.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin freeze \fINAME\fR \fR[\fB\-\- \fICMD\fR]\fR, \fBoci2bin thaw \fINAME\fR
Quiesce SQLite-backed volumes for an application-consistent snapshot, and
release it.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin checkpoint \fINAME\fR\fR, \fBoci2bin restore \fINAME\fR
Dump and restore a running named container with CRIU.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin sign \fR[\fB\-\-rekor\fR] [\fB\-\-attest \fIA\fR] \fB\-\-key \fIKEY\fR \fB\-\-in \fIBINARY\fR
Sign a binary (optionally publishing a Rekor transparency-log entry and/or an
in-toto attestation).
.B oci2bin verify \fB\-\-key \fIPUB\fR \fB\-\-in \fIBINARY\fR
checks it.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin pod run \fR[\fB\-\-net shared\fR] [\fB\-\-ipc shared\fR] \fIBINARY\fR ...
Run several binaries sharing namespaces.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin up \fR[\fB\-f \fIstack.yaml\fR] [\fB\-d\fR]\fR, \fBdown\fR, \fBstack \fR{\fBup\fR|\fBdown\fR|\fBlogs\fR|\fBconfig\fR}
Bring a declarative stack of binaries up and down (see the documentation for
the stack-file format).
.
.TP
.B oci2bin mcp\-serve \fR[\fB\-\-allow\-net\fR]
Serve the Model Context Protocol interface for AI-agent integration.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin from\-chroot \fIDIR\fR \fR[\fB\-o \fIOUT\fR] [\fB\-\-entrypoint \fICMD\fR] ...
Build a binary directly from a chroot directory — no Docker. Packs
.I DIR
into a single OCI layer.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin build\-dockerfile \fR[\fB\-f \fIFILE\fR] [\fB\-\-context \fIDIR\fR] ...
Build from a Dockerfile (BuildKit-compatible subset, incl.\&
.BR "RUN \-\-mount" ) without a Docker daemon.
.
.SH NAMESPACE SHARING
Two containers can share network or IPC namespaces using the
.B container:
.I PID
form of
.B \-\-net
and
.BR \-\-ipc .
This enables sidecar patterns and inter-container IPC without a shared daemon.
.PP
.B What is shared:
.TS
l l .
\fB\-\-net container:\fIPID\fR	Network interfaces, routing table, port bindings
\fB\-\-ipc container:\fIPID\fR	SysV semaphores, message queues, shmget/shmat memory
.TE
.PP
POSIX shared memory
.RB ( shm_open ,
.IR /dev/shm )
lives in the mount namespace and is not shared automatically.
Use
.B \-v /dev/shm:/dev/shm
to share the host
.IR /dev/shm ,
or
.BI "\-v /proc/" PID "/root/dev/shm:/dev/shm"
to share another container's
.IR /dev/shm .
.PP
Joining another container's namespace requires that both were started by a
process with matching user namespace ownership, or that the joining process
has root privileges.
If
.BR setns (2)
fails, a descriptive error is printed and the container exits.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.SS Run time (read by the produced binary)
.TP
.B OCI2BIN_DEBUG
Set to any value to print verbose runtime diagnostics (same as
.BR \-\-debug ).
.TP
.B OCI2BIN_TMPDIR
Directory for the runtime extraction tmpdir; tried before
.BR TMPDIR .
Point at a tmpfs for speed and to keep the rootfs off disk.
.TP
.B TMPDIR
Fallback extraction directory (then
.IR /tmp ", then " /var/tmp ).
.TP
.B OCI2BIN_IDENTITY
Path to the age identity (or SSH private key) used to decrypt an
.B \-\-encrypt
recipient image.
.TP
.B OCI2BIN_PASSWORD \fR/\fB OCI2BIN_PASSWORD_FILE
Passphrase (or a file whose first line is the passphrase) for a
.B \-\-passphrase
image.
.TP
.B OCI2BIN_CDI_DIR
Extra directory searched first for CDI specs, ahead of
.I /etc/cdi
and
.IR /run/cdi .
.TP
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
Path to the SSH agent socket forwarded when
.B \-\-ssh\-agent
is given.
.SS Build time (read by the oci2bin CLI)
.TP
.B AARCH64_SYSROOT \fR/\fB X86_64_SYSROOT
Override the sysroot used by the aarch64 / x86_64 cross-compiler.
aarch64 default:
.IR /usr/aarch64\-redhat\-linux/sys\-root/fc43 .
.TP
.B SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH
Fixed timestamp for
.B \-\-reproducible
/
.B \-\-offline\-only
builds.
.TP
.B VM_CPUS \fR/\fB VM_MEM_MB
Default vCPU count and memory (MiB) baked into a VM-mode binary.
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME \fR/\fB XDG_DATA_HOME
Override
.I ~/.cache
(build/layer caches) and
.I ~/.local/share
(detached-stack manifests, freeze tokens).
.TP
.B OCI2BIN_HOME
Override the directory where shared resources
.RI ( build_polyglot.py ,
pre-built loader binaries) are found.
Set automatically by
.B make install
to
.IR PREFIX/share/oci2bin .
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.cache/oci2bin/
Per-image build cache used by
.BR \-\-cache .
Each entry is a directory named
.IB image_digest /
containing the output binary.
.TP
.I /proc/self/exe
The loader reads its own OCI data by opening this path at runtime.
.TP
.I PREFIX/share/oci2bin/
Shared resources installed by
.BR "make install" :
.RS
.TP
.I build/loader\-x86_64
Pre-compiled static loader for x86_64.
.TP
.I build/loader\-aarch64
Pre-compiled static loader for aarch64.
.TP
.I scripts/build_polyglot.py
Polyglot builder script.
.TP
.I src/loader.c
Loader source code.
.RE
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status of the container process is propagated to the caller.
If the container process was killed by a signal, the exit status is 1.
If a fatal setup error occurs before exec, the exit status is 1.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Build examples
.EX
# Build from Docker Hub
oci2bin alpine:latest

# Explicit output name
oci2bin nginx:1.25 my\-nginx

# Cross-compile for aarch64
oci2bin \-\-arch aarch64 alpine:latest

# Build and cache
oci2bin \-\-cache redis:7\-alpine

# Strip documentation to reduce size
oci2bin \-\-strip ubuntu:22.04 my\-ubuntu

# Inject a config file at build time
oci2bin \-\-add\-file ./myapp.conf:/etc/myapp.conf myapp:latest

# Overlay debug tools onto a production image
oci2bin \-\-layer debugtools:latest myapp:latest myapp\-debug

# Build without Docker, from an OCI layout directory
skopeo copy docker://redis:7\-alpine oci:\&./redis\-oci:latest
oci2bin \-\-oci\-dir \&./redis\-oci redis:7\-alpine

# Build without a daemon in one step (skopeo pull backend)
oci2bin \-\-pull\-with skopeo redis:7\-alpine
.EE
.
.SS Runtime examples
.EX
# Run default entrypoint
\&./alpine_latest

# Override command
\&./alpine_latest /bin/ls /etc

# Terminate option parsing before a flag-like command
\&./alpine_latest \-\- \-v

# Volume mount
\&./alpine_latest \-v /data:/data /bin/ls /data

# Set environment variables
\&./alpine_latest \-e DEBUG=1 \-e HOME=/app /bin/sh

# Load environment from file
\&./my\-app \-\-env\-file /etc/myapp.env

# Read-only rootfs with writable scratch space
\&./my\-app \-\-read\-only \-\-tmpfs /tmp \-\-tmpfs /var/cache

# Run as non-root UID
\&./my\-app \-\-user 1000:1000

# Drop all capabilities, add back net_bind_service
\&./my\-app \-\-cap\-drop all \-\-cap\-add net_bind_service

# Isolated network namespace
\&./my\-app \-\-net none

# Share network namespace with another container (sidecar pattern)
\&./main\-app \-\-net none \-\-detach
\&./sidecar \-\-net container:$!

# Share IPC namespace
\&./service \-\-ipc container:$MAIN_PID

# Run in background, capture PID
PID=$(./redis \-\-detach)
kill "$PID"

# Init process for zombie reaping
\&./my\-app \-\-init
.EE
.
.SH HOW IT WORKS
The output file is a polyglot: simultaneously a valid ELF64 executable and a
valid POSIX tar archive.
.PP
The ELF magic bytes (0x7f\~E\~L\~F) appear at offset\~0; the ustar magic appears
at offset\~257.
The 64-byte ELF header is embedded inside the tar header's 100-byte filename
field so both formats coexist without conflict.
.PP
At runtime the loader:
.IP 1. 4
Opens itself via
.I /proc/self/exe
and reads the embedded OCI tar from the patched offset.
.IP 2. 4
Extracts image layers into a temporary rootfs under
.IR /tmp .
.IP 3. 4
Patches
.I /etc/passwd
and
.I /etc/group
for single-UID namespace compatibility.
.IP 4. 4
Enters a user namespace (host UID mapped to container UID\~0).
.IP 5. 4
Enters mount, PID, and UTS namespaces; optionally joins or creates a network
namespace and joins an IPC namespace.
.IP 6. 4
Applies volume bind mounts, then
.BR chroot (2)s
into the rootfs.
.IP 7. 4
.BR exec (2)s
the entrypoint.
.
